AN INTRIGUING RARITY - MONTILLA FROM SPAIN

Montilla deserves to be better known, It is grown in the chalky hills south of Cordoba and rivals Sherry in excellence, Its chief difference from Sherry is the fact that it is rarely fortified, thus yielding an alcohol strength below 18%. Like Sherry, it has its Finos, Olorosos and rare old wines. Those listed below come from Alvear, the oldest and most reliable of all the firms in Montilla,

Solera - a barrel laid down in 1750. Each year since then
